mage. Furthermore, Rhodiola henryi's neuroprotective and cardioprotective effects are also attributed to the presence of triterpenoid saponins.", "constituents": [], "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Rhodiola henryi are salidroside, rosarin, rosavin, and p-tyrosol. Salidroside is a unique glycoside that exhibits neuroprotective and antioxidant properties by scavenging free radicals and inhibiting lipid peroxidation. Rosarin, another phenylethanol glycoside, also possesses antioxidant properties and is known to have anti-inflammatory and anti-fatigue effects. Rosavin and p-tyrosol, which are responsible for Rhodiola's adaptogenic properties, have been shown to improve mental performance, reduce stress and anxiety, and inhibit the activity of MAO enzymes, thereby increasing neurotransmitter levels and enhancing mood. These constituents work synergistically to provide Rhodiola henryi with its therapeutic benefits, which include improved cognitive function, reduced fatigue, and enhanced mood stabilization.", "herb_names_common": [], "preparations": [{"name": "rhodiola extract", "mentions": 14, "confidence_score": 110, "total_score": 1540}, {"name": "rhodiola tincture", "mentions": 12, "confidence_score": 100, "total_score": 1200}, {"name": "rhodiola tea", "mentions": 12, "confidence_score": 94, "total_score": 1128}, {"name": "tea", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 69, "total_score": 552}, {"name": "tincture", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 63, "total_score": 504}, {"name": "capsules", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 57, "total_score": 456}, {"name": "rhodiola infusion", "mentions": 10, "confidence_score": 52, "total_score": 520}, {"name": "rhodiola capsules", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 50, "total_score": 400}, {"name": "infusion", "mentions": 6, "confidence_score": 39, "total_score": 234}, {"name": "rhodiola decoction", "mentions": 7, "confidence_score": 32, "total_score": 224}, {"name": "rhodiola extract capsules",